title: Add settle effect combinator
body:
This effect combinator will run effects in parallel and settle all effects before returning.

This is something that would be very useful for us, and I believe could be useful for others as well. When calling effects to fetch data in parallel, you may not want one failure to cause the other effects to be cancelled.

I was not sure what the desired response object should look like, so I left it simple and am open to changing it if there is something that would be better or more useful. While this is similar to [promise settling](http://bluebirdjs.com/docs/api/reflect.html), using the [PromiseInspection](http://bluebirdjs.com/docs/api/promiseinspection.html) interface didn't seem appropriate.

If you agree this is a useful effect combinator, I will write the docs for it. I didn't want to spend that time until this proposal was accepted and the response object format was agreed upon.

BTW - This is a great library, thank you for all your hard work!

cc - @spaintrain
